        <detaileddescription>
<para>saves mesh with optional selection to mru format; this is very convenient for saving intermediate states during algorithm debugging; &quot;.mrmesh&quot; save mesh format is not space efficient, but guaranties no changes in the topology after loading Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::serializeMesh</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>mesh</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>path</computeroutput> is a UTF-8 encoded filesystem path. Parameter <computeroutput>selection</computeroutput> defaults to a null pointer in C++. Parameter <computeroutput>serializeFormat</computeroutput> has a default argument: <computeroutput>&quot;.mrmesh&quot;</computeroutput>, pass a null pointer to use it. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput><ref refid="expected__void__std__string_8h_1a9638e07d2c5281b4bf574c618ab6f2e9" kindref="member">MR_expected_void_std_string_Destroy()</ref></computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
